This paper deals with the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for medical image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of multi-label segmentation, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of clinical data and picture archiving and communication systems (PACS), which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
